text: Goshen County is a county in the U.S. state of Wyoming. As of the 2020 census, 12,498 people lived there. Its county seat is Torrington. It is on the eastern border with Nebraska. == Communities == === City === * Torrington (county seat) === Towns === * Fort Laramie * La Grange * Lingle * Yoder === Census- designated places === * Hawk Springs * Huntley * Veteran === Unincorporated communities === * Jay Em * Rockeagle == References == == Other websites == * Official county website Category:1911 establishments in Wyoming Category:Wyoming counties
